        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 21 at 7:06PM CDT by NWS Twin Cities/Chanhassen MN</headline>
        <description>At 706 PM CDT, Law enforcement reported a strong thunderstorm near
Chokio, or 17 miles west of Morris, moving south at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Law enforcement reported.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Chokio.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
